  "title": "Junior Project Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities of Project Coordinator</p><p>•⁠ ⁠Assist Directors and Sales Managers in site surveys, prepare architectural briefs specific to projects, and lead project management.</p><p>•⁠ ⁠Close coordination with Production and Installation teams to ensure all works are delivered on time and with quality.</p><p>•⁠ ⁠Coordinate with sub-contractors, architects, consultants and relevant authorities to manage the progress and smooth execution of project.</p><p>•⁠ ⁠Ability to identify potential and occurring problems that affect the schedule of works at site and recommend solutions to relevant teams.</p><p>•⁠ ⁠Demonstrate exceptional multi-tasking skills and to know how to work out prelims, budgeting, monitor costs and quality, and to update all concerns and site management with verbal and written reports.</p><p>•⁠ Involved in method of statement and safety documents handling, with detailed drawings understanding and knowledge.</p><p><br /></p><p>Requirements of Project Manager</p><p>•⁠ Proficient use of AutoCAD.</p><p>•⁠ Able to communicate fluently.</p><p>•⁠ Bachelor's Degree in a relevant field or Diploma in Project Management.</p><p>•⁠ ⁠Basic use of MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint).</p><p>•⁠ Strong analytical, problem-solving skills, and project management experience.</p><p>•⁠ At least 2 years of project management experience or construction related experience.</p><p><br /></p><p>Monday to Friday 9am to 6pm</p>",
